    E1LinkPolicy⚓︎

    Groups parameters that define the policy relating to the use of E1 links.

    Field Type Label Description
    SctpPolicy SctpPolicy optional Contains parameters that define the policy for the use of SCTP on E1 links.

    Groups parameters that define the policy relating to the use of F1-c links.

    Field Type Label Description
    SctpPolicy SctpPolicy optional Contains parameters that define the policy for the use of SCTP on F1-c links.

    Groups parameters that define the policy relating to the use of NG-C links.

    Field Type Label Description
    SctpPolicy SctpPolicy optional Contains parameters that define the policy for the use of SCTP on NG-C links.

    Field Type Label Description

    SupportedPlmnSlices⚓︎

    Groups information about a PLMN and the set of slices supported by that PLMN.

    Field Type Label Description
    PlmnId string optional Identifies a PLMN.
    NbrOfSNssai uint32 optional automatically added field for "s-nssai" list
    SNssai SNssai repeated Identifies a slice that is supported by the PLMN.

    CellReselectionSubPriority⚓︎

    indicates a fractional value to be added to the value of cellReselectionPriority to obtain the absolute priority of the concerned carrier frequency for E-UTRA and NR

    Name Number Description
    o_2 0 0.2
    o_4 1 0.4
    o_6 2 0.6
    o_8 3 0.8

    CipheringAlgorithm⚓︎

    Type definition for 5G ciphering algorithms.

    Name Number Description
    nea0 0 NEA0, the null 5G ciphering algorithm.
    nea1 1 128-NEA1, the 128-bit SNOW 3G based 5G ciphering algorithm.
    nea2 2 128-NEA2, the 128-bit AES based 5G ciphering algorithm.
    nea3 3 128-NEA3, the 128-bit ZUC based 5G ciphering algorithm.

    mbw15 1

    genAccelleranGeneralTypes.proto⚓︎

    Ipv4Endpoint⚓︎

    Field Type Label Description
    Address string optional IPv4 address of the endpoint
    Port uint32 optional Port number to be used when the endpoint is the destination.

    Ipv4Interface⚓︎

    Field Type Label Description
    Address string optional IPv4 address of the interface
    SubnetMask string optional Subnet mask to be used on the interface
    Gateway string optional IP address of the default gateway to be used on the interface
    VlanId uint32 optional Optional VLAN ID to be used on the interface

    SctpParameters⚓︎

    Field Type Label Description
    IpAddress string optional The destination IPv4 address to be used for an SCTP association.
    Port uint32 optional The destination port to be used for an SCTP association.
    InStreams uint32 optional The number of inbound SCTP streams the initiator will accept.
    OutStreams uint32 optional The number of outbound SCTP streams the initiator wishes to establish. The peer entity may respond indicating that the number of streams it can accept is lower.

    AdminState⚓︎

    Administrative state of a managed object. The value locked means that the managed object is not allowed to operate. The value ulocked means that the managed object is allowed to operate.

    Name Number Description
    Locked 0
    UnLocked 1

    AltitudeRef⚓︎

    Name Number Description
    Wgs84 0 Altitude is with respect to the WGS-84 geoid
    MslGeoId 1 Altitude is with respect to the mean sea level geoid

    CellReserved⚓︎

    Indicates whether or not a cell is reserved for use by UEs belonging to Access Class 11 or 15.

    Name Number Description
    Reserved 0
    NotReserved 1

    OpState⚓︎

    Operational state of a managed object. The value enabled means that the managed object is capable of operating normally. The value disabled means that the managed object is not capable of operating normally (e.g. due to a fault condition).

    Name Number Description
    Enabled 0
    Disabled 1

    RfTxStatus⚓︎

    The RF transmit status of a cell. The value on-air means that the cell is transmitting and is able to provide service. The value off-air means that cell is not transmitting and is therefore not providing service.

    Name Number Description
    OnAir 0
    OffAir 1

    genAccelleranNeighbourRelations.proto⚓︎

    ExternalNrCellList⚓︎

    Contains a list of external neighbour relations, each containing a reference to a 5G NR external cell

    Field Type Label Description
    NbrOfExternalNrCell uint32 optional automatically added field for "external-nr-cell" list
    ExternalNrCell ExternalNrNbrCell repeated Each entry in this list represents an external NR cell.

    ExternalNrNbrCell⚓︎

    Field Type Label Description
    PlmnIdentity string optional
    NrCellIdentity uint64 optional
    NrGnbId uint32 optional GNB id for neighbour cell provided by dRax.
    NrGnbIdLength uint32 optional Number of valid bits for gNB Id provided by dRax.
    TargetTac uint32 optional TAC of the target cell cell
    PhysicalCellId uint32 optional The physical cell identity of the cell.
    Blacklisted bool optional True if the cell is to be included in the list of blacklisted cells for cell reselection purposes; otherwise false.
    SsbArfcn uint32 optional Absolute Radio Frequency(ARFCN) for the SS/PBCH block
    QOffsetCell PBAcc5GTypes.QOffsetRange optional
    QRxLevMinOffsetCell uint32 optional
    QRxLevMinOffsetCellSUL uint32 optional
    QQualMinOffsetCell uint32 optional
    SsbSubcarrierSpacing PBAcc5GTypes.SsbSubcarrierSpacing optional [3GPP 38.331] subcarrier spacing
    Smtc1 PBAcc5GTypes.SsbMtc optional
    FreqBandIndicator uint32 optional List of 5G frequency bands to perform measurements on.

    QQualMinOffsetCell uint32 optional

    DlCarrierFreq uint32 optional This field is deprecated and only here for backwards compatitbility with older dashboards. The CU ignores it and once these older versions of the dashboard are no longer in use it can be removed.
    DuplexMode PBAcc5GTypes.NrDuplexMode optional This field is deprecated and only here for backwards compatitbility with older dashboards. The CU ignores it and once these older versions of the dashboard are no longer in use it can be removed.

    genAccelleranNrUeMeasurements.proto⚓︎

    ReportConfigA3⚓︎

    Defines parameters that are configurable for all A3 report configurations (other than those in report-config-common).

    Field Type Label Description
    A3Offset int32 optional The offset value to be used in an A3 report configuration.
    TriggerQuantity TriggerQuantity optional Indicates whether A3 is to be based on RSRP or RSRQ or SINR measurements.
    Hysteresis uint32 optional The hysteresis parameter used in the entering and leaving conditions for an A3 event triggered reporting condition.
    TimeToTrigger TimeToTrigger optional The time during which the conditions for an A3 event need to be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

    ReportConfigCommon⚓︎

    Defines parameters that are configurable for all reportConfigs.

    Field Type Label Description
    MaxReportCells uint32 optional The maximum number of neighbour cells to be reported in the Measurement Report message.
    ReportInterval ReportInterval optional The interval between periodic reports. Can be applied to triggerType 'event' as well as 'periodical'.
    ReportAmount ReportAmount optional The number of measurement reports required. Can be applied to triggerType 'event' as well as 'periodical'.
    FilterCoeffRsrp PBAcc5GTypes.FilterCoefficient optional Filter coefficient for RSRP measurements at the UE
    FilterCoeffRsrq PBAcc5GTypes.FilterCoefficient optional Filter coefficient for RSRQ measurements at the UE
    FilterCoeffSinr PBAcc5GTypes.FilterCoefficient optional Filter coefficient for SINR measurements at the UE

    RegistrationRequestObject⚓︎

    Field Type Label Description
    UserId string optional The UR-ID per [n.12] R2-SRR-02 conformant per section 2.2 of [n.18].
    FccId string optional The FCC certification identifier of the CBSD. It is a string of up to 19 characters as described in [n.22]
    CbsdSerialNumber string optional A serial number assigned to the CBSD by the CBSD device manufacturer having a maximum length of 64 octets. This serial number shall be unique for every CBSD instance sharing the same value of fccId. Each CBSD has a single CBSD Antenna (Ref. definition in section 4) and has a single cbsdSerialNumber.
    CallSign string optional A device identifier provided by the FCC per [n.13].
    CbsdCategory CbsdCategory optional Device Category of the CBSD. Allowed values are 'A' or 'B' as defined in Part 96
    CbsdInfo CbsdInfo optional Information about this CBSD model.
    AirInterface AirInterfaceObject optional A data object that includes information on the air interface technology of the CBSD.
    InstallationParam InstallationParamObject optional A data object that includes information on CBSD installation.
    MeasurementCapabilities MeasurementCapabilitiesObject optional The array of string lists measurement reporting capabilities of the CBSD. The permitted enumerations are specified in [n.21].
    GroupingParam GroupingParam optional An array of data objects that includes information on CBSD grouping.
    CpiSignatureData CpiSignatureData optional The CPI is vouching for the parameters included in this object. In addition, the digital signature for these parameters is included.

    PduSessionCreateInfo⚓︎

    Contains information to create/delete a GTP tunnel for benchmark puropses

    Field Type Label Description
    PduSessionId uint32 optional The PDU Session will be created. Currently a PDU session can have only 1 tunnel
    TunnelId uint32 optional The tunnelId that will be created. Please not that MSB (most significant bit of the tunnel-id MUST be 0. It will be ignored anyway
    SimulatedDuIpAddress string optional The IPv4 address in dotted notation of the process that simulates the DU (downlink)
    SimulatedUpfIpAddress string optional The IPv4 address in dotted notation of the process that simulates the UPS (uplink)

    Field Type Label Description
    PduSessionId uint32 optional The pduSessionId that will be deleted.
    TunnelId uint32 optional The tunnelId that will be deleted. Please not that MSB (most significant bit of the tunnel-id MUST be 0. It will be ignored anyway

    Field Type Label Description
    items XpathItem repeated Carries max MAX_NUM_OF_XPATHS elements of type XpathItem

    FilterModeType⚓︎

    Specifies how you want filterinf done

    Name Number Description
    Filter_PREFIX 0 If the XPATH matches the beginning the filter will pass
    Filter_FULL 1 The XPATH must match exactly in order to pass
    Filter_LEAF 2 The XPATH must match exactly and the leaf must be matching in order to pass
    Filter_PREFIX_IGNORE_KEYS 3 If the XPATH matches the beginning the filter will pass (after the path was cleaned of keys attributes)
    Filter_FULL_IGNORE_KEYS 4 The XPATH must match exactly in order to pass (after the path was cleaned of keys attributes)
    Filter_LEAF_IGNORE_KEYS 5 The XPATH must match exactly and the leaf must be matching in order to pass (after the path was cleaned of keys attributes)

    Operation⚓︎

    Specifies what happend (Create Update Delete)

    Name Number Description
    Operation_UNKNOWN 0 The operation could not be determined
    Operation_CREATE 1 A create was done for the given xpath/leaf
    Operation_UPDATE 2 An update was done for the given xpath/leaf
    Operation_DELETE 3 A delete was done for the given xpath/leaf
    Operation_ALL 4 value to indicate that all operations are good

    Origin⚓︎

    Specifies where the modification came from

    Name Number Description
    Origin_APP 0 Modification was done by the application
    Origin_NETCONF 1 Modification was done via NetConf

    AdmissionControl⚓︎

    GnbCuCp⚓︎

    Grouping for the class representing a gNB-CU-CP.

    Field Type Label Description
    GnbId uint32 optional The gNB ID part of the Global gNB ID.
    PlmnId string optional 5 or 6 digit PLMN code (MCC and MNC) of the PLMN to which the gNB belongs. Forms part of the gNB's Global gNB ID as used in NGAP messages.
    GnbIdLength uint32 optional The length of the bit string representation of the gNB ID.
    GnbCuCpName string optional Human readable name of the gNB-CU-CP. If configured, this is sent to a gNB-CU-UP, gNB-DU and AMF during the E1, F1 and NG Setup procedures respectively.
    AdminState PBAccGenTypes.AdminState optional Administrative state. Value 'unlocked' means that the gNB is permitted to serve users. Value 'locked' means that the gNB is prohibited from serving users. In the 'locked' state, all of the gNB's cells will be off air.
    RlcMode PBAcc5GTypes.RlcMode optional Contains RLC mode entity value.
    OpState PBAccGenTypes.OpState optional Operational state. Value 'disabled' means that the gNB is totally inoperable and unable to provide service to users. Value 'enabled' means that the gNB is partially or fully operable and available for use.
    NbrOfAllowedCipheringAlgorithm uint32 optional automatically added field for "allowed-ciphering-algorithm" list
    AllowedCipheringAlgorithm PBAcc5GTypes.CipheringAlgorithm repeated List of 5G ciphering algorithms allowed to be used in the gNB, in decreasing order of preference, i.e. most preferred algorithm first. If nea0 is included, it should be the last entry in the list. Ciphering algorithms that are not supported by the gNB must not be included in the list.
    NbrOfAllowedIntegrityAlgorithm uint32 optional automatically added field for "allowed-integrity-algorithm" list
    AllowedIntegrityAlgorithm PBAcc5GTypes.IntegrityAlgorithm repeated List of 5G integrity algorithms allowed to be used in the gNB, in decreasing order of preference, i.e. most preferred algorithm first. nia0 should only be included in deployments where support of unauthenticated emergency calling is a regulatory requirement, and should be the last entry in the list. Integrity algorithms that are not supported by the gNB must not be included in the list.
    E1LinkPolicy PBAcc5GTypes.E1LinkPolicy optional Contains parameters that define the policy relating to the use of SCTP on E1 interfaces.
    F1CLinkPolicy PBAcc5GTypes.F1CLinkPolicy optional Contains parameters that define the policy relating to the use of SCTP on F1-c interfaces.
    NbrOfOperator uint32 optional automatically added field for "operator" list
    Operator Operator repeated Data relating to an operator who makes use of the gNB's services and resources. There may be more than one operator in the case of RAN sharing.

    genGNBCUUPTypes.proto⚓︎

    GnbCuUp⚓︎

    Represents a gNB-CU-UP.

    Field Type Label Description
    UpIntegrityProtectionEnabled bool optional Value true means that the CU-UP will activate integrity protection of DRBs if requested, subject to the specified integrity algorithm being supported; false means that it will not activate integrity protection of DRBs under any circumstances. This determines how the CU-UP handles receipt of a Security Indication IE with the Integrity Protection Indication IE set to 'required' or 'preferred', over E1.
    UpCipheringEnabled bool optional Value true means that the CU-UP will activate confidentiality protection of DRBs if requested, subject to the specified ciphering algorithm being supported; false means that it will not activate confidentiality protection of DRBs under any circumstances. This determines how the CU-UP handles receipt of a Security Indication IE with the Confidentiality Protection Indication IE set to 'required' or 'preferred', over E1.
